data.title: Kyrgyz leader keen on closer co
data.meta_description: Kyrgyz President Almazbek Atambayev believes that it's time for a closer cooperation with Azerbaijan.
data.text:
Kyrgyz President Almazbek Atambayev believes that it's time for a closer cooperation with Azerbaijan.

The president made this statement at the ceremony of the presentation of credentials by the Azerbaijani Ambassador to his country, Hidayat Orujov, the embassy said on Wednesday.

Azerbaijan attaches great importance to the development of cooperation with Kyrgyzstan in trade, economics, transport, communications, cultural and humanitarian affairs, Orujov said during his meeting with the president.

He said that he will make every effort for the development of cooperation between the two countries.

Azerbaijani President Ilham Aliyev signed a decree appointing Hidayat Orujov as Azerbaijan's Ambassador to Kyrgyzstan in December 2012.
